de.fu.junction.functional
Interface Function2<I,J,O>

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractFunction2, Differs, Equals, GenericFunction2, GreaterThan, GreaterThanOrEquals, InstanceOf, LessThan, LessThanOrEquals
@Author(value="Julian Fleischer")
public interface Function2<I,J,O>

A function that takes two parameters and results in one.

A function which goes from I -> J -> O, that is: a Method which takes 2 parameters and returns a result of type O.

Method Detail

asFunction

Function<I,O> asFunction(J $arg)
Retrieve a function which takes one parameter of type I only.

Essentially the resulting function is the same Function as this Function (i.e. the underlying method stays the same), but the given parameter is always applied as second parameter (i.e. the parameter which is of type J).

Parameters:
$arg - The argument to apply as second parameter.
Returns:
A two-dimensional Function-object representing this function which takes only one parameter.

asFunctionFlipped

Function<J,O> asFunctionFlipped(I $arg)
Retrieve a function which takes one parameter of type J only.

Essentially the resulting function is the same Function as this Function (i.e. the underlying method stays the same), but the given parameter is always applied as first parameter (i.e. the parameter which is of type I).

Parameters:
$arg - The argument to apply as first parameter.
Returns:
A two-dimensional Function-object representing this function which takes only one parameter.

call

O call(I $in1,
       J $in2)
Call this function with the parameters of type I and J and retrieve the result of type O.

Parameters:
$in1 - The first argument to apply.
$in2 - The second argument to apply.
Returns:
The result of the application of the two arguments.
